Test 3: Social Media Platform User Activity Analysis
Task Statement
"Go to a specific social media platform (Reddit, Twitter/X, or LinkedIn) and find a recent discussion thread (from the past 7 days) about 'quantum computing breakthroughs in 2024'. Identify: (1) The platform and specific thread URL, (2) At least 3 different users who commented, (3) What each user said (quote their key points), (4) One user's professional background if available, and (5) Any links or sources they shared. Cite the exact thread URL and quote the users accurately."

Required Deliverables
- Platform name and thread URL
- At least 3 different usernames
- Quoted key points from each user
- One user's professional background
- Links/sources shared by users
- All information from past 7 days
- Direct thread URL citation

Success Criteria
- At least 5 search actions executed
- Thread is from past 7 days (date verification)
- At least 3 distinct users identified
- User quotes are accurate and attributed
- Professional background found for at least one user
- Thread URL is valid and accessible
- Information demonstrates actual platform visit and reading
- At least 2 distinct sources (platform thread + any shared links)

