Test 4: Obscure Historical Event with Multiple Perspectives
Task Statement
"Find information about the 'Great Emu War' that occurred in Australia. Provide: (1) The exact year it took place, (2) The specific region/location, (3) The number of emus involved (if available), (4) The outcome and why it's considered notable, (5) A quote from a primary source (government document, newspaper article, or official record from that time period), and (6) How modern historians or researchers view this event. Cite at least one primary source and one modern analysis."

Required Deliverables
- Exact year of the event
- Specific location/region
- Number of emus (if documented)
- Outcome and historical significance
- Quote from primary source (contemporary document)
- Modern historical perspective
- Primary source citation
- Modern analysis citation
- At least 4 distinct sources

Success Criteria
- At least 7 search actions executed
- Historical facts are accurate and specific
- Primary source quote is from the time period
- Modern perspective is included
- At least one primary source cited (government/newspaper/archive)
- At least one modern analysis cited
- Information demonstrates research across time periods
- At least 4 distinct sources cited

