Test 5: Multi-Domain Esoteric Knowledge Synthesis
Task Statement
"Find and synthesize information about: (1) The exact chemical formula and IUPAC name for the compound used in non-stick cookware coatings (Teflon), (2) The name and location of the company that first commercially produced this material, (3) The year it was first used in cookware, (4) One documented health concern or controversy related to this material, including a specific study or report, and (5) A current alternative material being used and one company that manufactures cookware with this alternative. For each item, provide the specific data, a citation URL, and explain how the information connects to create a complete picture."

Required Deliverables
- Chemical formula and IUPAC name for Teflon compound
- Original commercial producer company name and location
- Year of first cookware use
- Health concern with specific study/report
- Current alternative material
- Company manufacturing alternative cookware
- Citation URL for each of the 5 items
- Synthesis explaining connections
- At least 6 distinct sources

Success Criteria
- At least 8 search actions executed
- All 5 items have specific, accurate data
- Chemical information is precise (formula and IUPAC name)
- Historical information includes company and location
- Health concern cites specific study/report
- Alternative material and company are current/real
- Each item has a valid citation URL
- Synthesis demonstrates understanding of connections
- At least 6 distinct authoritative sources cited
- Information spans chemistry, history, health, and current products
